{"source_key":"sha256-c8597aca71664a84bdd657ea13dadbd3","record_index":469,"record_hash":"sha256:5d107720f8315a00bd2f031b7059c9e6c50ac57405a5e9ba9f20676d61113e10","timestamp":"2026-05-20T01:43:10.122Z","kind":"tool_call","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:custom_tool_call","role":null,"text":null,"tool_name":"apply_patch","tool_input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: /Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 [REDACTED:entropy].md\n@@\n-Turn identity should be derived from capture content, not from time or provider\n-turn ids. A good shape is:\n+Turn identity should be derived from capture content, not from time or provider\n+turn ids:\n \n ```text\n-turn-key = hash(session_key + source_key + ordered_new_record_hashes)\n+turn-key = sha256-hex16(session_key + NUL + source_key + NUL + ordered_new_record_hashes)\n ```\n@@\n - capture timestamp\n - transcript record membership, probably by record hash and/or source record\n   index\n - optional provider turn key on transcript records, for grouping/display only\n-- optional previous turn reference, if it can be made meaningful\n+- previous turn reference, when there is a previous capture turn in the same\n+  session\n - environment snapshot\n@@\n Capture turns are the durable agentlog concept. Provider turns are useful for UI\n grouping when available, but they are not portable enough to define the storage\n model across agents.\n+\n+Store `previous_turn_key` as a session-wide previous capture turn pointer when\n+it is available. It is not part of turn identity. It exists to make interval\n+evidence cheap to evaluate, for example \"worktree files seen in the previous\n+turn later appeared in commits visible in this turn.\" The first turn omits the\n+field.\n@@\n-- checked-out references, if this is not already represented by stacks\n \n Plain Git mode should still fit the shape. The checked-out branch can be treated\n as a one-branch stack, while still using GitButler libraries where possible.\n@@\n-The \"checked-out references\" field may duplicate the stack/branch structure. It\n-should either be folded into the stack representation or kept only as a derived\n-query shape. This needs a design decision.\n+Do not store a separate `checked_out_refs` field. It duplicates the stack/branch\n+snapshot and creates reader precedence questions. Also do not store graph\n+projection internals such as `is_entrypoint`; that is a traversal detail, not\n+durable product evidence for association.\n@@\n-Example shape:\n+Use a path cap of 256 entries per path list. Keep the total count even when the\n+list is not truncated. It is redundant in the common case, but useful for\n+consistent reads and essential when `*_truncated = true`.\n+\n+Example worktree shape:\n \n ```json\n {\n-  \"worktree_files\": [\"src/foo.rs\", \"src/bar.rs\"],\n-  \"worktree_file_count\": 2,\n-  \"worktree_files_truncated\": false\n+  \"files\": [\"src/foo.rs\", \"src/bar.rs\"],\n+  \"file_count\": 2,\n+  \"files_truncated\": false\n }\n ```\n@@\n If a list exceeds the cap, store the first capped set in deterministic sorted\n order plus the total count and `*_truncated = true`. Path hashes can be added\n later if matching beyond the cap becomes necessary, but they should not be part\n of the first shape.\n+\n+Do not store commit message summaries in the turn snapshot. Commit subjects can\n+be read from Git by `commit_id` when a UI needs them, and they are not useful\n+association evidence.\n+\n+Concrete turn detail example:\n+\n+```json\n+{\n+  \"schema\": \"gitbutler.agent-session-turn.v1\",\n+  \"turn_key\": \"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\n+  \"session_key\": \"sha256-1122334455667788\",\n+  \"source_key\": \"sha256-9988776655443322\",\n+  \"previous_turn_key\": \"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\n+  \"captured_at\": \"2026-05-20T18:42:11.123Z\",\n+  \"records\": [\n+    {\n+      \"source_key\": \"sha256-9988776655443322\",\n+      \"record_index\": 42,\n+      \"record_hash\": \"sha256:abc123...\"\n+    }\n+  ],\n+  \"environment\": {\n+    \"snapshot_status\": \"complete\",\n+    \"worktree\": {\n+      \"files\": [\n+        \"crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs\",\n+        \"crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs\"\n+      ],\n+      \"file_count\": 2,\n+      \"files_truncated\": false\n+    },\n+    \"stacks\": [\n+      {\n+        \"stack_id\": \"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\n+        \"branches\": [\n+          {\n+            \"name\": \"agentlog-turns\",\n+            \"review\": {\n+              \"pull_request\": 1284,\n+              \"review_id\": null\n+            },\n+            \"commits\": [\n+              {\n+                \"commit_id\": \"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\n+                \"change_id\": \"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\n+                \"files\": [\n+                  \"crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs\",\n+                  \"crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs\"\n+                ],\n+                \"file_count\": 2,\n+                \"files_truncated\": false\n+              }\n+            ]\n+          }\n+        ]\n+      }\n+    ]\n+  }\n+}\n+```\n+\n+Omit null and empty optional fields in storage where possible. The example keeps\n+some nulls visible only to show the conceptual shape.\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T01:43:10.122Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}